{% from "components/chat-list/macro.njk" import chatList %}
{% from "components/chat-list-item/macro.njk" import chatListItem %}
{% from "components/chat-message/macro.njk" import chatMessage %}

<h2>Polite live region</h2>
<p>The list has <code>role="log"</code> and <code>aria-live="polite"</code>
  so screen readers announce new messages when the user is idle.</p>

{% call chatList() %}
  {% call chatListItem() %}
    {{ chatMessage({ origin: "peer", author: "Nurse", text: "Hi there" }) }}
  {% endcall %}
  {% call chatListItem() %}
    {{ chatMessage({ origin: "self", author: "You", text: "Hi" }) }}
  {% endcall %}
{% endcall %}

<h2>Assertive live region</h2>
<p>Use <code>live: "assertive"</code> only for messages that must
  interrupt the user immediately — for example, a clinician urgently
  needing acknowledgement. Prefer <code>polite</code> in most cases.</p>
